snippet: LEAD: Asian-Americans on the West Coast have yet to exert political power commensurate with their growing numbers and economic might, but they are beginning to identify issues that bring a measure of political unity to their diverse population....
lead_paragraph: LEAD: Asian-Americans on the West Coast have yet to exert political power commensurate with their growing numbers and economic might, but they are beginning to identify issues that bring a measure of political unity to their diverse population.

headline.main: Diversity Hinders Asians' Power in U.S.

byline.original: By JANE GROSS, Special to The New York Times
